  "formulas": {
    "equations": [
      "\\Delta V_k = r_k^* \\Delta z_k \\Delta r_k \\Delta \\theta_k",
      "\\iiint_G f(r,\\theta,z) dV = \\iiint f(r,\\theta,z) r \\, dz \\, dr \\, d\\theta",
      "\\Delta V_k = \\rho_k^{*2} \\sin\\phi_k^* \\Delta\\rho_k \\Delta\\phi_k \\Delta\\theta_k",
      "\\iiint_G f(\\rho,\\theta,\\phi) dV = \\iiint f(\\rho,\\theta,\\phi) \\rho^2 \\sin\\phi \\, d\\rho \\, d\\phi \\, d\\theta",
      "x = r \\cos\\theta",
      "y = r \\sin\\theta",
      "x = \\rho \\sin\\phi \\cos\\theta",
      "y = \\rho \\sin\\phi \\sin\\theta",
      "z = \\rho \\cos\\phi",
      "z = \\sqrt{25 - r^2}",
      "z = 9 - r^2",
      "\\rho \\cos\\phi = \\rho \\sin\\phi"
    ],
    "aiExplanation": "These formulas summarize the volume elements for cylindrical and spherical coordinates, applying the necessary 'r' and 'ρ² sin(φ)' scale factors. They correspond directly to the graphed volumes, defining the bounds for surfaces like cones, spheres, cylinders, and paraboloids."
